<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-07-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-07-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                                Indonesia/7–648: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Consulate General</gloss> at
                                    Batavia</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-07-06T19:00:00-04:00">July
                                        6, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>320. <gloss target="#t_Usgoc1">Usgoc</gloss> 119. Reports from Lake
                                Success reach Dept to effect that Critchley preparing new action
                                designed to surmount present impasse negotiations. Dept uninformed
                                character such action. In order to avoid prejudice position new
                                    <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> and for other reasons
                                Dept hopes you will reserve your position Aus suggestion pending
                                Dept’s receipt details and your receipt Dept’s comments thereon.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>